	# Routines
	--> Adverbs Of Indefinite Frequency	Belirsiz Sıklık Zarfları
		-----------	always / all the time		   		I always drink coffee before 09:00
		 ----------	almost always / nearly always			She nearly always says the same thing
		  ---------	very often / constantly				He very often goes to the restroom
		   --------	usually / generally		   		I am usually late for meetings
		    -------	normally / regularly		   		What time do you normally go to bed?
		     ------	often / frequently	           		We often / frequently play football at weekends
		      -----	sometimes / occasionally / from time to time	Sometimes I (occasionally) play 52 cards with my friends
		       ----	seldom / infrequently				He seldom does my homework
			---	rarely						I rarely go to the gym
			 --	hardly ever/scarcely ever/almost never		I hardly ever read the newspaper
			  .	never						They never listen to what he says
										Mom always said life was like a box of chocolates. 
											You never know what you're gonna get.
										
        			S			V	O
							
				S	Adv. of Freq.	V	O
				he	generally	steals	a phone
				she	almost always	listens to music
				they	regularly	draw	designs
				I	frequently	try to reach my aim
				he	often		talks much to his friends
				they	rarely		make mistake at work
				we	seldom		go shopping at weekends
				you	never		interfere
				I 	never 		suffer along my life
				He	never		regret from what I do
				I	generally	live to the fullest
				I  was	hardly ever	fooled in my life 
				
				S	M	Adv. of Freq.	V	O
				she 	can 	always		beat	me				
		
			- things don't always go with the way you want them to be		işler her zaman istediğin gibi gitmez		
			- every so often it comes to my mind					arada sırada aklıma geliyor	
		


	--> Adverbs Of Definite Frequency	Belirli Sıklık Zarfları		How often?

		once        a day                   	daily = everyday != nightly     day-ly    every day
		twice       a week                  	weekly
		three times a month                 	monthly
		four times  a year                  	yearly
        						annually                anniversary
        						hourly
    	
		every day/week/month/year           ever != never
    		every two days                       (+) != (-)
    		every three weeks                       hiç
    		every six months
    
    		- she visits the dentist twice a year
    		- this magazine is published monthly.
    		- he visits his mother once a week.
    		- I work five days a week.
    		- I saw the movie seven times.
    		- he goes to the gym three times a week
    		- we pay our mortgage every month
    		- there is a leap day every four years
    		- I call her daily to make sure she is fine








