What do you see in front of you?	I see laptop in front of me
Where does he read?			He reads an english book in the library
Who do you drink with?			I drink with my family
Whose car lost?
Whose car do you see?			I see my father's car
What dont you come to the school for?	I dont come to the school, because I am ill
How many cars do you have?		I have 2 cars
How much gas is left in the car?	Half depot of gas is left in the car
How long do you learn English in the course?	I learn English in the course for a month





--> STATIC VERBS
MENTAL STATE      EMOTIONAL STATE      POSSESSION STATE      SENSE PERCEPTIONS       OTHERS
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
think *           love                 possess               see *                   look *
realize           like                 have *                smell *                 owe
understand        dislike              own                   hear                    be *
suppose           loathe               belong to             feel *                  seem *
forget            hate                                       taste *                 cost
notice            detest                                                             sound
prefer            appreciate                                                         exist
feel *            fear                                                               appear *
believe           forgive                                                            weigh *
recognize         envy                                                               advise
mean              mind                                                               promise
doubt             wish                                                               consist of
imagine           care                                                               refuse
know              desire                                                             include
remember                                                                             contain
want                                                                                 
need



			static = non-progressive 		!= 	dynamic = progressive
			---------------------------------------------------------------------
			simple						continuous
			perfect						perfect continuous
			---------------------------------------------------------------------
	think		sanmak						düşünmek		
	see		görmek						görüşmek
	smell		kokmak						koklamak
	taste		tadından bahsetmek				tatmak
	look		gibi gözükmek					bakmak
	appear		gibi görünmek					ortaya çıkmak
	weigh		ağırlığından bahsetmek				tartmak
	
	

-> think
          sanmak, zannetmek	---> I think this city is really beautiful
	  			---> I think she is a student
                            	---> I think they will visit us next week
			    	---> I think this is the beginning of a beautiful friendship
          düşünmek          	---> I'm thinking about going abroad next year 
                            	---> She is thinking about her family
-> see
          görmek		---> I see lots of people in the street
	  			---> I see dead people
          görüşmek		---> The doctor is seeing his patient now
                    		---> The manager is seeing the applicant now.
-> smell
          kokmak    		---> This perfume smells very nice.
                    		---> These flowers smell awful.
				---> My mom smells like flowers
          koklamak  		---> My mom is smelling the flowers.	 
				---> Why are you smelling the milk?
-> taste
          tadından söz etmek 	---> This soup tastes awful. I can't eat it. 
                             	---> The dinner looks bad but tastes delicious.
          tadına bakmak      	---> My husband are tasting my dish right now. 
-> feel
          sezinlemek, ummak 	---> This pillow feels very hard.
                            	---> I feel (that) something bad will happen.
          hissetmek         	---> I feel better now./I'm feeling better now. 
-> look
          gibi görünmek     	---> You look ill. You'd better go home.
                            	---> That ladder doesn't look safe.
          bakmak            	---> Why are you looking out of the window?
-> appear
          gibi görünmek     	---> the teacher appears to be in a bad mood today. 
                            	---> She appears to be bored with the film.
          (ortaya) çıkmak   	---> The comedian is appearing nightly at the Broken Door club.
-> weigh
          ağırlık söylerken 	---> The baby weighs three kilograms.
          tartmak           	---> The butcher is weighing the meat now.
-> be
          genel bir durum	---> You are very rude				Kabasın
          anlık değişen durum	---> You are being rude				Kabalaşıyorsun
	  			     He is just being modest			Mütavazi oluyor sadece
				     
-> have
          sahiplik bildiriyorsa	---> she doesn't have much money now. She has two brothers.
          eylem bildiriyorsa    ---> he is having breakfast now.
                                ---> he is having a shower right now.



---> PRESENT CONTINUOS TENSE
AM
Q --> am I coming to her birthday party?
A --> yes, you are coming...
N --> no, you are not coming...
IS
Q --> is he/she coming to her birthday party?
A --> yes, he/she is coming...
N --> no, he/she is not coming...
ARE
Q --> are you coming to her birthday party?
A --> yes, I am coming...
N --> no, I'm not coming...
ARE
Q --> are we/you/they coming to her birthday party?
A --> yes, we/you/they are coming...
N --> no, we/you/they are not coming...

	Present Continous Signals: 			Examples:
		now		(şimdi)			- it is raining outside now
		right now	(şu anda)		- my friend and I are working on a creative project right now
		at the moment	(şu anda)		- I am eating lunch at the moment. Can I call you back in an hour?
		at present	(şu ara)		- they are dealing with a project nowadays
		these days	(bu günlerde)		- she is working as a food engineer in a factory these days
		nowadays	(bu günlerde)		- he is repairing cars nowadays 
		still		(halen)			- I am still studying for tomorrow's exam
		today		(bugün)			- I am baking a big cake for my friend's birthday
		tonight 	(bu gece)		- I am watching telly tonight				(for present use)
							- I will watch telly tonight				(for future use)

---> MAKING A QUESTION FOR PRESENT CONTINUOUS
				        |	    S		|	V	|	O	|
5 W 1 H		   |     QUESTIONS 	|    	SUBJECT		|      VERB	|     OBJECT	|
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
what		   |   		            			|    need	|
which + NOUN	   |   am		    I			|    seeing	|
what kind of + NOUN|		         			|    looking	|
-------------------|   are		    YOU			|    walking	|
where              |		         			|    running	|
where  ... to/from |   is	            HE			|    want	|
-------------------|   is	            SHE			|    reading	|
when X             |   is	            IT (Lesson)		|    writing	|
what time X	   |   		            			|    spending	|
-------------------|   are		    WE			|    watching	|
who    ... to/with |   are		    YOU			|    drinking	|
whom		   |   are		    THEY (Lessons)	|    eating	|
whose + NOUN	   |		         			|    making	|
-------------------|   		         			|    doing	|
why		   |			 			|    starting	|
what 	  ... for  |		         			|    solving	|
-------------------|		         			|    listening	|
how		   |		         			|    hear	|
how many + NOUN	   |		         			|    wearing	|
how much + NOUN	   |		         			|    talking	|
