---> PRESENT PERFECT CONTINUOUS TENSE
HAS BEEN V3
Q --> has he/she been living in Milano?
A --> yes, he/she has been living in Milano
N --> no, he/she has not been living in Milano
HAVE BEEN V3
Q --> have you been living in Milano?
A --> yes, I have been living in Milano
N --> no, I have not been living in Milano

	Present Perfect Continuous Signals: 
		for			- he has been working in this company for twenty five years
		since			- he has been working in this company since 1996
		how long		- how long has he been working in this company? 
		lately			- Idk what has been bothering you lately, but if I've done something, I wish you would tell me.
		recently		- I've been studying English for a few years and recently decided to branch out on my own.
		all morning		- they have been trying to work the prototype all morning
		all day	/ the whole day	- you've been sleeping all day.
		all year		- they have been developing a project on Autonomous Mobile Robots all year
		
		

