---> FUTURE TIME
--> WILL
Rapid Decision    – I am thirsty. I think I will buy a drink.
Offer             – That looks heavy, I will help you with it.
Promise           – Don’t worry. I won’t tell anyone.
Threat            – If you don’t stop I will tell your mother.
Refusal           – She won’t listen to anything I say.

--> TO BE GOING TO
Prior plan: The decision was made before the moment of speaking.
	                – I am going to the beach next weekend with my friends.
Evidence/Signs(Certainty): When there are signs that sth is likely to happen.
	                – My stomach hurts a lot. I think I am going to throw up.

--> THE STORY: FATHER, SON and DAUGHTER
               D - dad, will we study together tonight?
               F - okay, we will study
               after a while...
               S - dad, will we study together tonight?
               F - no, I am going to study with your sister
                   no, I won't study with you tonight
               S - then I won't study on my own

Future Simple Signals: 
	tomorrow
	the day after tomorrow
	tonight
	soon
	next week
	in a week/month
	in two days
	in three days
	in four weeks

Future Continuous Signals: 
	this time
	next week
	-- and other expressions with future reference

Future Perfect Signals: 
	before
	by
	by then
	by the time
	until
	till

	I will have already arrived at that hour - ben o saate çoktan varmış olacağım
	
	
Future Perfect Continuous Signals: this tense is not used very much
	by, by then, by the time, for


WAS / WERE GOING TO
i was going to call you but my battery died - seni arayacaktım ama şarjım bitti
i was going to leave it but i forgot - onu bırakacaktım ama unuttum
they were going to come to visit but - ziyaret etmeye geleceklerdi ama



gördüğüm şey	what I see
yaptığım şey	what I do
duyduğum şey	what I hear
				

how good are you
how well are you seeing
